<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1437,906,2013]" pageId="1" pageNumber="183">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,380,1051,1077]" pageId="1" pageNumber="183">Mature nymph</emphasis>
(in alcohol): 
<emphasis box="[530,608,1051,1077]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="183">Length</emphasis>
: Body 
<quantity box="[690,827,1050,1077]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.35" metricValueMax="3.5" metricValueMin="3.2" pageId="1" pageNumber="183" unit="mm" value="3.35" valueMax="3.5" valueMin="3.2">3.2–3.5 mm</quantity>
; cerci 
<quantity box="[899,1034,1051,1077]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.2" metricValueMax="1.3" metricValueMin="1.1" pageId="1" pageNumber="183" unit="mm" value="1.2" valueMax="1.3" valueMin="1.1">1.1–1.3 mm</quantity>
(
<figureCitation box="[1049,1137,1051,1077]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="2.[151,250,1954,1978]" captionTargetBox="[175,1412,181,1930]" captionTargetId="figure-17@2.[175,1412,181,1930]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURE 1. Nigrobaetis klugei sp. nov. A) Mature nymph; B) Tergal coloration of immature nymph; C) Immature nymph; D) Antennae close to each other" figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5840737" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5840737/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="183">Fig. 1A</figureCitation>
); terminal filament shorter in female (
<quantity box="[271,408,1087,1113]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="7.5" metricValueMax="8.0" metricValueMin="7.0" pageId="1" pageNumber="183" unit="mm" value="0.75" valueMax="0.8" valueMin="0.7">0.7–0.8 mm</quantity>
) than in male (0.9–1.0 mm).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1437,906,2013]" pageId="1" pageNumber="183">
<emphasis box="[151,283,1123,1149]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="183">Coloration:</emphasis>
Head uniformly brown without vermiform marks on vertex and frons. Eyes of male nymphs reddish brown, thorax dark brownish without any pattern. Legs generally whitish, dorsal side of femora with a brown band at 2/3 distally and dark brown apically (
<figureCitation box="[600,763,1195,1221]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="4.[151,250,1927,1951]" captionTargetBox="[185,1403,181,1903]" captionTargetId="figure-17@4.[185,1403,181,1903]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURE 3. Nigrobaetis klugei sp. nov. A) Foreleg; B) Dorsal view of forefemur; C) Ventral view of forefemur; D) Midleg; E) Hindleg; F) Foreclaw; G) Postero-tergal spines of segment VII; H) Abdomen; I) Gill IV; J) Whorls of spines in cerci; K) Paraproct. Abbreviations: G–Gill, HWp–Hindwing pad, PTs- Postero-tergal spines" figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5840743" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5840743/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="183">Figs 3B &amp; 3C</figureCitation>
). Abdominal tergite I light brownish, tergites II and III dark brownish, tergite IV light brownish, tergites V-VII dark brownish, tergite VIII light brownish; tergite IX whitish; tergite X dark brownish without any spots (coloration paler in younger specimens) (
<figureCitation box="[1102,1257,1267,1293]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="2.[151,250,1954,1978]" captionTargetBox="[175,1412,181,1930]" captionTargetId="figure-17@2.[175,1412,181,1930]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURE 1. Nigrobaetis klugei sp. nov. A) Mature nymph; B) Tergal coloration of immature nymph; C) Immature nymph; D) Antennae close to each other" figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5840737" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5840737/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="183">Figs 1B&amp; 1C</figureCitation>
). Entire surface of tergites covered with scales. Abdominal sternites I to 
<collectionCode box="[773,793,1303,1329]" country="Canada" lsid="urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:13946" name="Royal British Columbia Museum - Herbarium" pageId="1" pageNumber="183" type="Museum">V</collectionCode>
light brown; sternites 
<collectionCode box="[1041,1071,1303,1329]" country="Norway" name="Mykotektet, National Veterinary Institute" pageId="1" pageNumber="183">VI</collectionCode>
and 
<collectionCode box="[1123,1162,1303,1329]" pageId="1" pageNumber="183">VII</collectionCode>
dark brownish; sternites VIII and IX paler. Cerci dark brownish in proximal part and paler in the distal part.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1437,906,2013]" pageId="1" pageNumber="183">
<emphasis box="[199,260,1375,1401]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="183">Head</emphasis>
: Antennae close to each other (
<figureCitation box="[603,691,1375,1401]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="2.[151,250,1954,1978]" captionTargetBox="[175,1412,181,1930]" captionTargetId="figure-17@2.[175,1412,181,1930]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURE 1. Nigrobaetis klugei sp. nov. A) Mature nymph; B) Tergal coloration of immature nymph; C) Immature nymph; D) Antennae close to each other" figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5840737" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5840737/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="183">Fig. 1D</figureCitation>
). Labrum: dorsal surface (
<figureCitation box="[980,1067,1375,1401]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1938,1962]" captionTargetBox="[166,1422,190,1914]" captionTargetId="figure-20@3.[165,1422,181,1914]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 2. Nigrobaetis klugei sp. nov. A) Labrum; B) Hypopharynx; C) Left mandible (arrow indicates minute spines between prostheca and mola); D) Right mandible; E) Maxilla; F) Labium; G) Glossa and Paraglossa" figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5840741" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5840741/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="183">Fig. 2A</figureCitation>
) with 1+3 long simple stout setae on the distal half and 6-7 small simple setae scattered on the surface; ventral surface with three to four small pointed setae near lateral margin; distal margin with two kinds of setae: laterally 7 to 8 long, feathered setae and medially shorter, slightly feathered setae. Hypopharynx: lingua trilobed, covered with small simple setae; superlinguae with thin setae apically and laterally (
<figureCitation box="[534,626,1519,1545]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1938,1962]" captionTargetBox="[166,1422,190,1914]" captionTargetId="figure-20@3.[165,1422,181,1914]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 2. Nigrobaetis klugei sp. nov. A) Labrum; B) Hypopharynx; C) Left mandible (arrow indicates minute spines between prostheca and mola); D) Right mandible; E) Maxilla; F) Labium; G) Glossa and Paraglossa" figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5840741" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5840741/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="183">Fig. 2B</figureCitation>
). Incisors of left mandible (
<figureCitation box="[956,1045,1519,1545]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1938,1962]" captionTargetBox="[166,1422,190,1914]" captionTargetId="figure-20@3.[165,1422,181,1914]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 2. Nigrobaetis klugei sp. nov. A) Labrum; B) Hypopharynx; C) Left mandible (arrow indicates minute spines between prostheca and mola); D) Right mandible; E) Maxilla; F) Labium; G) Glossa and Paraglossa" figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5840741" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5840741/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="183">Fig. 2C</figureCitation>
) with 6 denticles; prostheca with 7 broad denticles and a reduced comb-shaped structure; margin between prostheca and mola proximally with 2 large spines and distally with 5 minute spines; tuft of setae at apex of mola absent. Incisors of right mandible (
<figureCitation captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1938,1962]" captionTargetBox="[166,1422,190,1914]" captionTargetId="figure-20@3.[165,1422,181,1914]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 2. Nigrobaetis klugei sp. nov. A) Labrum; B) Hypopharynx; C) Left mandible (arrow indicates minute spines between prostheca and mola); D) Right mandible; E) Maxilla; F) Labium; G) Glossa and Paraglossa" figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5840741" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5840741/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="183">Fig. 2D</figureCitation>
) with 8 denticles; prostheca with 7 denticles; margin between prostheca and mola with 11-12 medium pointed spines; tuft of setae at apex of mola present. Maxillae (
<figureCitation box="[778,864,1663,1689]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1938,1962]" captionTargetBox="[166,1422,190,1914]" captionTargetId="figure-20@3.[165,1422,181,1914]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 2. Nigrobaetis klugei sp. nov. A) Labrum; B) Hypopharynx; C) Left mandible (arrow indicates minute spines between prostheca and mola); D) Right mandible; E) Maxilla; F) Labium; G) Glossa and Paraglossa" figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5840741" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5840741/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="183">Fig. 2E</figureCitation>
) with 3 broad canines; absence of setae at base of canines, 3 setae at base of lacinia; palp two-segmented; segment I approximately 1.1 x length of segment II; segment II apically rounded, covered with thin setae. Labium (
<figureCitation box="[779,869,1735,1761]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1938,1962]" captionTargetBox="[166,1422,190,1914]" captionTargetId="figure-20@3.[165,1422,181,1914]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 2. Nigrobaetis klugei sp. nov. A) Labrum; B) Hypopharynx; C) Left mandible (arrow indicates minute spines between prostheca and mola); D) Right mandible; E) Maxilla; F) Labium; G) Glossa and Paraglossa" figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5840741" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5840741/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="183">Fig. 2F</figureCitation>
): Glossae slightly shorter than paraglossae; inner margin of glossae with a row of 10–11 setae; paraglossae as wide as glossae (
<figureCitation box="[1021,1111,1771,1797]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1938,1962]" captionTargetBox="[166,1422,190,1914]" captionTargetId="figure-20@3.[165,1422,181,1914]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 2. Nigrobaetis klugei sp. nov. A) Labrum; B) Hypopharynx; C) Left mandible (arrow indicates minute spines between prostheca and mola); D) Right mandible; E) Maxilla; F) Labium; G) Glossa and Paraglossa" figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5840741" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5840741/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="183">Fig. 2G</figureCitation>
), falcate, with long and stout setae on outer margin and dorsally 4 long simple setae near inner margin; labial palp three-segmented, segment I subrectangular and subequal in lengths to segment II and III combined; simple small setae on the lateral margin of segment I; segment II with a dorsal oblique row of three long pointed setae; segment III truncated and apically rounded with medium to small pointed setae.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1437,906,2013]" lastBlockId="6.[151,1437,151,1149]" lastPageId="6" lastPageNumber="188" pageId="1" pageNumber="183">
<emphasis box="[199,289,1951,1977]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="183">Thorax:</emphasis>
Foreleg (
<figureCitation box="[404,497,1951,1977]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="4.[151,250,1927,1951]" captionTargetBox="[185,1403,181,1903]" captionTargetId="figure-17@4.[185,1403,181,1903]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURE 3. Nigrobaetis klugei sp. nov. A) Foreleg; B) Dorsal view of forefemur; C) Ventral view of forefemur; D) Midleg; E) Hindleg; F) Foreclaw; G) Postero-tergal spines of segment VII; H) Abdomen; I) Gill IV; J) Whorls of spines in cerci; K) Paraproct. Abbreviations: G–Gill, HWp–Hindwing pad, PTs- Postero-tergal spines" figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5840743" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5840743/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="183">Fig. 3A</figureCitation>
). Femora. Villopore absent, outer margin of femora with about 11 stout, apically rounded setae with minute hairs (
<figureCitation box="[535,625,1987,2013]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="4.[151,250,1927,1951]" captionTargetBox="[185,1403,181,1903]" captionTargetId="figure-17@4.[185,1403,181,1903]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURE 3. Nigrobaetis klugei sp. nov. A) Foreleg; B) Dorsal view of forefemur; C) Ventral view of forefemur; D) Midleg; E) Hindleg; F) Foreclaw; G) Postero-tergal spines of segment VII; H) Abdomen; I) Gill IV; J) Whorls of spines in cerci; K) Paraproct. Abbreviations: G–Gill, HWp–Hindwing pad, PTs- Postero-tergal spines" figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5840743" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5840743/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="183">Fig. 3B</figureCitation>
); inner margin with 13-14 small stout setae which are variable in size. Tibiae. Outer margin with 11 small simple setae; inner margin with 9-10 spines, with a single large comb-shaped, unipinnate seta and a bipinnate seta present on its apex (
<figureCitation box="[786,876,187,213]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="4.[151,250,1927,1951]" captionTargetBox="[185,1403,181,1903]" captionTargetId="figure-17@4.[185,1403,181,1903]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURE 3. Nigrobaetis klugei sp. nov. A) Foreleg; B) Dorsal view of forefemur; C) Ventral view of forefemur; D) Midleg; E) Hindleg; F) Foreclaw; G) Postero-tergal spines of segment VII; H) Abdomen; I) Gill IV; J) Whorls of spines in cerci; K) Paraproct. Abbreviations: G–Gill, HWp–Hindwing pad, PTs- Postero-tergal spines" figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5840743" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5840743/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="188">Fig. 3A</figureCitation>
). Tarsi. Outer margin with ca. 8 small stout setae; inner margin with 8-9 spines. Tarsal claws (
<figureCitation box="[658,744,223,249]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="4.[151,250,1927,1951]" captionTargetBox="[185,1403,181,1903]" captionTargetId="figure-17@4.[185,1403,181,1903]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURE 3. Nigrobaetis klugei sp. nov. A) Foreleg; B) Dorsal view of forefemur; C) Ventral view of forefemur; D) Midleg; E) Hindleg; F) Foreclaw; G) Postero-tergal spines of segment VII; H) Abdomen; I) Gill IV; J) Whorls of spines in cerci; K) Paraproct. Abbreviations: G–Gill, HWp–Hindwing pad, PTs- Postero-tergal spines" figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5840743" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5840743/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="188">Fig. 3F</figureCitation>
) hooked with one row of about 11 acute teeth increasing in size towards apex. Midleg (
<figureCitation box="[465,557,259,285]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="4.[151,250,1927,1951]" captionTargetBox="[185,1403,181,1903]" captionTargetId="figure-17@4.[185,1403,181,1903]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURE 3. Nigrobaetis klugei sp. nov. A) Foreleg; B) Dorsal view of forefemur; C) Ventral view of forefemur; D) Midleg; E) Hindleg; F) Foreclaw; G) Postero-tergal spines of segment VII; H) Abdomen; I) Gill IV; J) Whorls of spines in cerci; K) Paraproct. Abbreviations: G–Gill, HWp–Hindwing pad, PTs- Postero-tergal spines" figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5840743" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5840743/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="188">Fig. 3D</figureCitation>
). Outer margin of femora with about 8 stout, apically rounded setae and with minute hairs; inner margin with 11-12 small stout setae. Tibiae. Outer margin with 11 small simple setae present; inner margin with 9 small spines present. Tarsi. Outer margin with 7-8 small simple setae; inner margin with 5 small spines. Claws of mid and hind legs similar to that of foreleg. Hindleg (
<figureCitation box="[931,1017,367,393]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="4.[151,250,1927,1951]" captionTargetBox="[185,1403,181,1903]" captionTargetId="figure-17@4.[185,1403,181,1903]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURE 3. Nigrobaetis klugei sp. nov. A) Foreleg; B) Dorsal view of forefemur; C) Ventral view of forefemur; D) Midleg; E) Hindleg; F) Foreclaw; G) Postero-tergal spines of segment VII; H) Abdomen; I) Gill IV; J) Whorls of spines in cerci; K) Paraproct. Abbreviations: G–Gill, HWp–Hindwing pad, PTs- Postero-tergal spines" figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5840743" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5840743/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="188">Fig. 3E</figureCitation>
). Outer margin of femora with 9 stout apically rounded setae. Tibiae. Outer margin bare; inner margin with 10 small spines. Outer margin of tarsi bare; inner margin with 5 small spines. Hindwing pads present (
<figureCitation box="[804,895,439,465]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="4.[151,250,1927,1951]" captionTargetBox="[185,1403,181,1903]" captionTargetId="figure-17@4.[185,1403,181,1903]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURE 3. Nigrobaetis klugei sp. nov. A) Foreleg; B) Dorsal view of forefemur; C) Ventral view of forefemur; D) Midleg; E) Hindleg; F) Foreclaw; G) Postero-tergal spines of segment VII; H) Abdomen; I) Gill IV; J) Whorls of spines in cerci; K) Paraproct. Abbreviations: G–Gill, HWp–Hindwing pad, PTs- Postero-tergal spines" figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5840743" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5840743/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="188">Fig. 3G</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
