<paragraph blockId="6.[151,1437,151,1149]" pageId="6" pageNumber="188">
<emphasis box="[199,305,475,501]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="188">Abdomen</emphasis>
: Tergites with numerous scale bases, posterior margin with long and pointed triangular spines in segments I to X (
<figureCitation box="[352,483,511,537]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="4.[151,250,1927,1951]" captionTargetBox="[185,1403,181,1903]" captionTargetId="figure-17@4.[185,1403,181,1903]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURE 3. Nigrobaetis klugei sp. nov. A) Foreleg; B) Dorsal view of forefemur; C) Ventral view of forefemur; D) Midleg; E) Hindleg; F) Foreclaw; G) Postero-tergal spines of segment VII; H) Abdomen; I) Gill IV; J) Whorls of spines in cerci; K) Paraproct. Abbreviations: G–Gill, HWp–Hindwing pad, PTs- Postero-tergal spines" figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5840743" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5840743/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="188">Figs 3G–H</figureCitation>
). Gills on segments I to 
<collectionCode box="[770,812,511,537]" pageId="6" pageNumber="188">VII</collectionCode>
; gill I elongated and reduced (
<figureCitation box="[1165,1258,511,537]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="4.[151,250,1927,1951]" captionTargetBox="[185,1403,181,1903]" captionTargetId="figure-17@4.[185,1403,181,1903]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURE 3. Nigrobaetis klugei sp. nov. A) Foreleg; B) Dorsal view of forefemur; C) Ventral view of forefemur; D) Midleg; E) Hindleg; F) Foreclaw; G) Postero-tergal spines of segment VII; H) Abdomen; I) Gill IV; J) Whorls of spines in cerci; K) Paraproct. Abbreviations: G–Gill, HWp–Hindwing pad, PTs- Postero-tergal spines" figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5840743" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5840743/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="188">Fig. 3H</figureCitation>
); gills II to 
<collectionCode box="[1397,1436,511,537]" pageId="6" pageNumber="188">VII</collectionCode>
elliptic with dark margin, relatively long setae and serrated all along margins, tracheation well visible but poorly divided (
<figureCitation box="[250,327,583,609]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="4.[151,250,1927,1951]" captionTargetBox="[185,1403,181,1903]" captionTargetId="figure-17@4.[185,1403,181,1903]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURE 3. Nigrobaetis klugei sp. nov. A) Foreleg; B) Dorsal view of forefemur; C) Ventral view of forefemur; D) Midleg; E) Hindleg; F) Foreclaw; G) Postero-tergal spines of segment VII; H) Abdomen; I) Gill IV; J) Whorls of spines in cerci; K) Paraproct. Abbreviations: G–Gill, HWp–Hindwing pad, PTs- Postero-tergal spines" figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5840743" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5840743/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="188">Fig. 3I</figureCitation>
). Whorls of spines on cerci large and triangular in shape reaching 1/2 of the corresponding segment (
<figureCitation box="[160,238,619,645]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="4.[151,250,1927,1951]" captionTargetBox="[185,1403,181,1903]" captionTargetId="figure-17@4.[185,1403,181,1903]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURE 3. Nigrobaetis klugei sp. nov. A) Foreleg; B) Dorsal view of forefemur; C) Ventral view of forefemur; D) Midleg; E) Hindleg; F) Foreclaw; G) Postero-tergal spines of segment VII; H) Abdomen; I) Gill IV; J) Whorls of spines in cerci; K) Paraproct. Abbreviations: G–Gill, HWp–Hindwing pad, PTs- Postero-tergal spines" figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5840743" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5840743/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="188">Fig. 3J</figureCitation>
). Paraproct (
<figureCitation box="[380,467,619,645]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="4.[151,250,1927,1951]" captionTargetBox="[185,1403,181,1903]" captionTargetId="figure-17@4.[185,1403,181,1903]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURE 3. Nigrobaetis klugei sp. nov. A) Foreleg; B) Dorsal view of forefemur; C) Ventral view of forefemur; D) Midleg; E) Hindleg; F) Foreclaw; G) Postero-tergal spines of segment VII; H) Abdomen; I) Gill IV; J) Whorls of spines in cerci; K) Paraproct. Abbreviations: G–Gill, HWp–Hindwing pad, PTs- Postero-tergal spines" figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5840743" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5840743/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="188">Fig. 3K</figureCitation>
) with abundant scale bases, but almost no setae and reduced number of spines on distal margin (three large and two small spines); postero-lateral extension with scale bases, margin with numerous blunt, triangular, small spines.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="6.[151,1437,151,1149]" box="[199,402,727,753]" pageId="6" pageNumber="188">
