<subSubSection pageId="6" pageNumber="188" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="6.[151,1437,151,1149]" pageId="6" pageNumber="188">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,324,762,788]" pageId="6" pageNumber="188">Diagnosis:</emphasis>
<taxonomicName authority="Sivaruban &amp; Srinivasan &amp; Barathy &amp; Isack, 2022" authorityName="Sivaruban &amp; Srinivasan &amp; Barathy &amp; Isack" authorityYear="2022" box="[331,538,763,789]" class="Insecta" family="Baetidae" genus="Nigrobaetis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Ephemeroptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="188" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="klugei" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[331,538,763,789]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="188">Nigrobaetis klugei</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[546,636,763,789]" pageId="6" pageNumber="188">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[546,636,763,789]" pageId="6" pageNumber="188" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
can be differentiated from other Oriental species of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Novikova &amp; Kluge" authorityYear="1987" box="[1228,1359,763,789]" class="Insecta" family="Baetidae" genus="Nigrobaetis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Ephemeroptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="188" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1228,1359,763,789]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="188">Nigrobaetis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by the following combination of characters: (i) dorsal surface of the labrum with 1+3 long simple stout setae on the distal half (
<figureCitation box="[209,299,835,861]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1938,1962]" captionTargetBox="[166,1422,190,1914]" captionTargetId="figure-20@3.[165,1422,181,1914]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 2. Nigrobaetis klugei sp. nov. A) Labrum; B) Hypopharynx; C) Left mandible (arrow indicates minute spines between prostheca and mola); D) Right mandible; E) Maxilla; F) Labium; G) Glossa and Paraglossa" figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5840741" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5840741/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="188">Fig. 2A</figureCitation>
); (ii) paraproct distally not expanded, with a reduced number of spines on distal margin (
<figureCitation box="[1285,1374,835,861]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="4.[151,250,1927,1951]" captionTargetBox="[185,1403,181,1903]" captionTargetId="figure-17@4.[185,1403,181,1903]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURE 3. Nigrobaetis klugei sp. nov. A) Foreleg; B) Dorsal view of forefemur; C) Ventral view of forefemur; D) Midleg; E) Hindleg; F) Foreclaw; G) Postero-tergal spines of segment VII; H) Abdomen; I) Gill IV; J) Whorls of spines in cerci; K) Paraproct. Abbreviations: G–Gill, HWp–Hindwing pad, PTs- Postero-tergal spines" figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5840743" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5840743/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="188">Fig. 3K</figureCitation>
); (iii) paraglossae slender, approx. as wide as glossae (
